### Step-by-Step Workflow (say this clearly)

**"The complete user journey has 3 phases:"**

**PHASE 1 — Setup (Teacher)**
```
Teacher logs in → JWT token issued → stored in browser localStorage
→ Teacher creates quiz (manual/PDF/topic)
→ Server calls Gemini API → questions generated
→ Quiz saved to MongoDB with unique 6-digit join code
→ Teacher starts live room → Socket.IO room created
```

**PHASE 2 — Live Session**
```
Student enters join code → server verifies quiz is active
→ Student socket joins the room (socket.join(quizId))
→ Teacher clicks START → server broadcasts 'quiz_started' to ALL sockets in room
→ Server emits 'sync_timer' with server-calculated endTime
→ Student submits answer → socket event fires to server
→ Server validates answer → updates MongoDB Result → recalculates leaderboard
→ Server broadcasts progress update + new leaderboard to ALL in room
→ Teacher sees real-time colored grid | Students see live rankings
```

**PHASE 3 — Conclusion**
```
Teacher clicks END (or timer expires automatically)
→ Server marks all Results as 'completed' in MongoDB
→ Final leaderboard computed and saved to Quiz document
→ 'quiz_ended' broadcast → all clients navigate to leaderboard page
→ Results permanently accessible for analytics
```

