## Q9: What is the architecture pattern used and why?

### 🏆 RANK 1 ANSWER:
> *"Our system follows a **3-Tier Architecture**:*
>
> *The **Presentation Tier** is the React + Vite frontend. It has no direct database access and contains only UI logic — rendering, user interaction, and API calls. This separation ensures the frontend can be independently deployed (we have a [vercel.json](file:///c:/Users/manim/OneDrive/Desktop/kahoot_team2026/Demo_project/client/vercel.json) for Vercel deployment).*
>
> *The **Application Tier** is the Node.js + Express backend. It contains all business logic: authentication, quiz creation, AI generation, scoring, and real-time event handling. This is the only tier that knows how to talk to both the frontend and the database. Socket.IO runs on this tier, bridging the real-time gap.*
>
> *The **Data Tier** is MongoDB Atlas — a cloud-hosted database. It stores all persistent data. All access goes through Mongoose ODM (Object Document Mapper), which provides schema validation, relationship management, and an expressive query API.*
>
> *Additionally, we integrate **external services** — Google Gemini API for AI generation and MongoDB Atlas as a cloud service.*
>
> *Within the frontend, we use the **Provider Pattern** (React Context API) for global state management — this avoids prop drilling and gives all components access to authentication state. On the backend, we use the **MVC (Model-View-Controller)** pattern: Models (`/models`), business logic Controllers (`/controllers`), and Routes (`/routes`) map HTTP endpoints to controller functions."*

